AMD now has the lead in fake launches and artificial scarcity for no other reason than they simply didn't make more... 
Remember when you could go into a store, say "I would like to make a pre-order for XYZ", then the clerk would happily take down your information, charge you accordingly, give you a RECEIPT OF PAYMENT for that product, and the number of reserves was a known quantity that would be acquired from the manufacturer for release to the purchaser on launch day.
